==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Induviæ
<hw>In*du"vi*⟦ae⟧</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L.,
clothes, fr. <ets>induere</ets> to put on. See <er>Indue</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Persistent portions of a calyx or corolla; also,
leaves which do not disarticulate from the stem, and hence remain for a
long time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Induviate</ent>⟦br⟧
